    <h1 style="color: #EC0808; text-align:center;">LaunchPad API</h1>

    <br/><br/>
    <h2>What is Launchpad API?</h2>
    <p>
      LaunchPad API is a service that allows websites to integrate social sign-ins in less than 5 minutes. <br/>
      Developers tend to spend a lot of time (and money) reading and implementing OAuth API documentations for various social platforms
      such as Facebook, Twitter, GitHub, LinkedIn, Google, etc. <br/>
      We know the pain of reading OAuth API documents, so we made it easy for you <br/>
      With 2 lines of code, LaunchPad helps your website handle OAuth requests. <br/>
    </p>

  <br/>
  <h2>Give me a Demo!</h2>

  <div id="launchpad"></div>

  <br/>
  <h2>Usage</h2>

    <h3 style="font-weight: normal">1. Place an empty <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> to wherever you want the LaunchPad to be located</h3>

    <pre class="prettyprint linenums" style="width:auto;"><ol class="linenums"><li class="L0"><span class="tag">&lt;body</span><span class="tag">&gt;</span></li><li class="L0"><span class="tag">...</span></li><li class="L0">    <span class="tag">&lt;div</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="atn">id</span><span class="pun">=</span><span class="atv">"launchpad"</span><span class="tag">&gt;</span><span class="tag">&lt;/div</span><span class="tag">&gt;</span></li><li class="L0"><span class="tag">...</span></li><li class="L0"><span class="tag">&lt;/body</span><span class="tag">&gt;</span></li></ol></pre>

    <h3 style="font-weight: normal">2. Include LaunchPad and fire</h3>
    <p>On the bottom of the page, include the <a href="https://raw.github.com/harrychenca/launchpad/master/app/assets/javascripts/launchpad.js">JavaScript file</a> and call launchpad(elementId, callbackUrl): <br/>
    <ul>
      <li><i>elementId</i>: id of the empty div (e.g "launchpad")</li>
      <li><i>callbackUrl</i>: page that handles the response of the API call</li>
    </ul>
    </p>

<pre class="prettyprint linenums" style="width:auto;"><ol class="linenums"><li class="L0"><span class="tag">&lt;script</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="atn">src</span><span class="pun">=</span><span class="atv">"https://raw.github.com/harrychenca/launchpad/master/app/assets/javascripts/launchpad.js" </span><span class="atn">type</span><span class="pun">=</span><span class="atv">"text/javascript"</span><span class="tag">&gt;</span><span class="tag">&lt;/script&gt;</span><li class="L0"><span class="tag">&lt;script</span><span class="pln"> </span><span class="atn">type</span><span class="pun">=</span><span class="atv">"text/javascript"</span><span class="tag">&gt;</span><li><span>	launchpad("launchpad", "http://www.callback_to_your_site.com/");</span></li><li class="L0"><span class="tag">&lt;/script</span><span class="tag">&gt;</span></li ></ol></pre>

  <h3 style="font-weight: normal">If OAuth is <b>successful</b>:</h3>
  <p>
    A GET request is sent to the <i>callbackUrl</i> you specified with following parameters: <code>name, email, picture_url</code>
    and one of <code>facebook_url, github_url, linkedin_url, twitter_url, google_url</code>
  </p>

  <h3 style="font-weight: normal">If OAuth is <b>not successful</b>:</h3>
  A GET request with a error message is sent to the <i>callbackUrl</i>.

